The article announces several nominations and appointments made by the United States government. Roxanne Cabral has been nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States to the Republic of the Marshall Islands. Kelly Craft has been nominated to be the Representative of the United States to the United Nations, as well as the Representative in the Security Council of the United Nations. Joshua Deahl has been nominated to be an Associate Judge of the District of Columbia Court of Appeals, and Deborah Israel has been nominated to be an Associate Judge of the Superior Court of the District of Columbia. John Kramer has been nominated to be the Chief Financial Officer of the Department of Transportation. Lastly, Paul Shmotolokha has been nominated to be the First Vice President of the Export-Import Bank of the United States.